article.headline: Norfolk State 79, Hampton 64
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Curtis Bunn scored 18 points and Norfolk State used a 13-3 run late in the first half to blow open a tight game and defeat Hampton 79-64 Sunday night. Calvin Brown scored on a layup, two free throws and a stickback after Tony Murphy's missed 3-pointer as the Spartans (3-3, 2-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) stretched a 27-23 lead to 40-26 at the break. Hampton (3-5, 1-2 MEAC) could not cut the lead to less than double digits the rest of the way. The Pirates raced to a 9-0 lead. Norfolk State broke the drought with 15:25 to go in the first half when Karandick Ogunride hit a pair of free throws, then took the lead for good on Brown's free throw to make it 15-13 with 9:16 left in the half. Norfolk State was 8-of-17 on 3-pointers while Hampton was only 4-of-20. The Spartans also were 15-of-20 from the line. The Pirates were 6-of-9. Bunn came off the bench to lead four Hampton players in double figures. Chakowby Hicks scored 17, Brown had 16 and Murphy 10. Bruce Brown had 12 points and 12 rebounds for Hampton. Rashad West also scored 12 points, and Adrian Woodard added 10.
